t","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-wisdom-al-hikmah","tag-barley-al-shair","tag-bread-al-khubz","tag-food-al-taam","tag-gluttony-al-siman","tag-hunger-al-juu","tag-manners-adab","tag-prophetic-virtues-manaqib-nabawi","tag-satiety-al-shiba","tag-temperance-asceticism-zuhd"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-6Lj","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":26036,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/03\/12\/prophet-full-stomach-khubz\/","url_meta":{"origin":25997,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Food: The Prophet never filled his stomach with bread","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 12, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, left this world while he had never ate to his fill of barley bread. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5098 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062e\u064e\u0631\u064e\u062c\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25985,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/02\/26\/refined-processed-white-flour\/","url_meta":{"origin":25997,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Bread: Caution against refined, processed white flour","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 26, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Hazm reported: He asked Sahl, \u201cDid you see refined flour in the time of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him?\u201d Sahl said no. He said, \u201cWould you sift the barley flour?\u201d Sahl said, \u201cNo, but we would blow the husks from it.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5094 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34527,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/10\/28\/prophet-suffers-with-sahabah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25997,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Hunger: The Prophet suffers in poverty with his companions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 28, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Talhah reported: We complained about hunger to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and we lifted our garments to reveal stones tied to our stomachs, so the Messenger of Allah lifted his garment to reveal two stones. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2371 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":797,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/20\/prophet-business-yahud\/","url_meta":{"origin":25997,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Trade: The Prophet has business relations with Jews","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, passed away while his armor was mortgaged to a Jew for thirty portions of barley. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 2916, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1603 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u062a\u064f\u0648\u064f\u0641\u0650\u0651\u064a\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17319,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/12\/26\/restrain-burping-no-overeating\/","url_meta":{"origin":25997,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Eating: Hold back your burping, do not overeat","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 26, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Juhayfah reported: I ate a stew of bread and fattened meat. Then, I came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and I belched loudly. The Prophet said, \"Restrain your belching. Verily, those who ate to their fill the most in this world will be the hungriest\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":784,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/05\/15\/ahl-al-bayt-eat-fill\/","url_meta":{"origin":25997,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Food: The Prophet\u2019s family rarely ate to their fill","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 15, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The family of Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him,\u00a0never ate to their fill of wheat bread for three consecutive nights, ever since they had come to Medina, until he passed away. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6089, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2970 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25997","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=25997"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25997\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=25997"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=25997"},{"taxonomy":"